comment: * [icu enhancement] ICU's replacement for {@link java.lang.Character.UnicodeBlock}. Methods, fields, and other functionality specific to ICU are labeled '[icu]'. * * A family of character subsets representing the character blocks in the * Unicode specification, generated from Unicode Data file Blocks.txt. * Character blocks generally define characters used for a specific script * or purpose. A character is contained by at most one Unicode block. * * [icu] Note: All fields named XXX_ID are specific to ICU.

variables.name: GREEK_ID
variables.comment: * Unicode 3.2 renames this block to "Greek and Coptic".

variables.name: COMBINING_MARKS_FOR_SYMBOLS_ID
variables.comment:
* Unicode 3.2 renames this block to "Combining Diacritical Marks for
         * Symbols".

variables.name: PRIVATE_USE_AREA_ID
variables.comment:
* Same as public static final int PRIVATE_USE.
         * Until Unicode 3.1.1; the corresponding block name was "Private Use";
         * and multiple code point ranges had this block.
         * Unicode 3.2 renames the block for the BMP PUA to "Private Use Area"
         * and adds separate blocks for the supplementary PUAs.

variables.name: PRIVATE_USE_ID
variables.comment:
* Same as public static final int PRIVATE_USE_AREA.

variables.name: CYRILLIC_SUPPLEMENTARY_ID
variables.comment: * Unicode 4.0.1 renames the "Cyrillic Supplementary" block to "Cyrillic Supplement".

variables.name: COUNT
variables.comment:
* One more than the highest normal UnicodeBlock value.
         * The highest value is available via UCharacter.getIntPropertyMaxValue(UProperty.BLOCK).
         *
         * @deprecated ICU 58 The numeric value may change over time, see ICU ticket #12420.
         * @hide unsupported on Android

variables.name: BLOCKS_
variables.comment: * Array of UnicodeBlocks, for easy access in getInstance(int)

methods.name: public static UnicodeBlock getInstance(int id)
methods.comment: * [icu] Returns the only instance of the UnicodeBlock with the argument ID. * If no such ID exists, a INVALID_CODE UnicodeBlock will be returned. * @param id UnicodeBlock ID * @return the only instance of the UnicodeBlock with the argument ID * if it exists, otherwise a INVALID_CODE UnicodeBlock will be * returned.

methods.name: public static UnicodeBlock of(int ch)
methods.comment:
* Returns the Unicode allocation block that contains the code point,
         * or null if the code point is not a member of a defined block.
         * @param ch code point to be tested
         * @return the Unicode allocation block that contains the code point

methods.name: public static final UnicodeBlock forName(String blockName)
methods.comment: * Alternative to the {@link java.lang.Character.UnicodeBlock#forName(String)} method. * Returns the Unicode block with the given name. [icu] Note: Unlike * {@link java.lang.Character.UnicodeBlock#forName(String)}, this only matches * against the official UCD name and the Java block name * (ignoring case). * @param blockName the name of the block to match * @return the UnicodeBlock with that name * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the blockName could not be matched

methods.name: public int getID()
methods.comment:
* {icu} Returns the type ID of this Unicode block
         * @return integer type ID of this Unicode block

methodNames: public static final UnicodeBlock forName(String blockName)
